## 11. OC-11: `workspace_root_is_non_git_local_master`

{{PROJECT_VAR_BRACE}} is a non-git local master. Claude Code prompts must not include `git commit` or `git push` for it. The git repo for the common docs and the `src/` mirror is {{REPO_VAR_BRACE}}.

## 12. OC-12: `src_mirror_sync`

The `src/` mirror under {{REPO_VAR_BRACE}} reflects the workspace source `{{PROJECT_VAR_BRACE}}/src/`. Do not edit the mirror directly; modify the workspace source and run `make sync-src` when the task is a source sync.

<!-- endif -->
<!-- if:ENABLE_AUTO_MODE=yes -->
## 13. OC-13: `auto_mode_workspace_isolation`

Auto mode never edits existing project files in place. It uses an isolated task workspace.

Implications:

- The workspace source, datasets, checkpoints, result directories, and notebooks are read-only during Auto mode campaigns.
- Claude Code copies required source files into `${CLAUDE_DIR}/{TASK_ID}/workspace/src/` and mutates only that copy.
- Experiment outputs, run-local checkpoints, results, logs, and patches go under `${CLAUDE_DIR}/{TASK_ID}/`.
- The campaign deliverable is a patch proposal with evidence; applying it to the workspace is a separate explicit task.
- Fair comparison is tier-based: the case subset, epochs, seed, batch size, score aggregation, and metric parser must match inside a tier.

<!-- endif -->
Conditional OC numbers (OC-11 and above) may be absent when the corresponding subsystem is off in this clone, and that is fine; the OC identifiers stay stable regardless.

